","relationship":"student","years":"circa 1830","institution_blurb":"Educated at Hudson — Western Reserve College's preparatory academy founded by his father."}],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"education":[{"institution":"Hudson, Ohio","notes":"Educated at Hudson Ohio."},{"institution":"Oberlin College","notes":"Oberlin College, intending ministry but failing health prevented."}],"career":[{"title":"Vocal music teacher","type":"music","notes":"Possessed a beautiful voice; considered a wonderful singer."},{"title":"Chorister","organization":"Congregational Church Austinburg OH","dates":">20 years","type":"religion","notes":"Chorister at Congregational Church Austinburg for 20+ years."},{"title":"Farmer","type":"agriculture","notes":"Also a farmer in Austinburg."}],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"education","header":"Educated at Hudson, then Oberlin College","body":"Lewis prepared at the Western Reserve College academy in Hudson — the institution his father had helped found — and went on to Oberlin College, the abolitionist school that admitted Black students from its 1833 founding. The choice of Oberlin marked his alignment."},{"number":2,"category":"arts","header":"Voice teacher across the Reserve for two decades","body":"After graduation Lewis worked as a singing-master through the towns of the Western Reserve, training choruses and parish choirs. He earned a regional reputation as a teacher of voice."},{"number":3,"category":"religion","header":"Chorister at his father's church for twenty years","body":"Lewis led the music of the Austinburg church his father had built — the same congregation his sisters Martha and Cornelia sang in — for over twenty years. He died at forty-nine, still serving the choir."}],"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM035","plot_notes":"Austinburg Center Cemetery, Austinburg, Ashtabula County, Ohio."},"slug":"lewis-cowles-1812"},"HD3721":{"id":"HD3721","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendant